object.customQuery:
SELECT distinct task.SystemId, 
task.ParentId, 
task.CMMContainer, 
task.Id, 
task.UpdateCount, 
task.UpdateUser, 
task.UpdateTimestamp, 
task.Version, 
task.TemplateId, 
task.Name, 
task.Priority, 
task.Description, 
task.OriginalOwner, 
task.OriginalOwnerCd, 
task.Text, 
task.WorkDt, 
task.CriticalDtInd, 
task.CriticalDt, 
task.ReminderInd, 
task.ReminderDt, 
task.ReportToInd, 
task.ReportTo, 
task.ReportToCd, 
task.RepeatingInd, 
task.Note, 
task.Comments, 
task.AddedByUserId, 
task.Status, 
task.AddDt, 
task.AddTm, 
task.CompleteDt, 
task.CompleteTm, 
task.CompletedByUserId, 
task.WorkRequiredInd, 
task.CurrentOwner, 
task.CurrentOwnerCd, 
task.EscalatedInd, 
task.NotificationRequestRef, 
task.FromEmail, 
task.ToEmail, 
task.ReplyToEmail, 
task.Subject, 
task.GoverningStateCd, 
task.ProductName, 
task.LicenseClassCd, 
task.CarrierGroupCd, 
task.CarrierCd, 
task.PolicyTypeCd, 
task.PolicyGroupCd, 
task.AssignedProducerCd, 
task.AssignedProducerName, 
task.AgencyCd, 
task.AgencyName, 
task.AgencyGroupCd, 
task.AgencyGroupName, 
task.LossCauseCd, 
task.ExaminerCd, 
task.ExaminerName, 
task.BranchCd, 
task.InSIUInd, 
task.DOIComplaintInd, 
task.CatastropheInd, 
task.ClaimStatus, 
task.InjuryInvolvedInd, 
task.SubrogationId, 
task.InstallmentNumber, 
task.CustomerName, 
task.ServicingProducerCd, 
task.ServicingProducerName, 
task.RowId 
FROM
 task task 
where task.Systemid in (
select systemid from advrxxchangedbeans where concat(adddt,addtm)>='$$m_strtdt' and concat(adddt,addtm) <='$$m_Enddt' and
 cmmcontainer='Task'
)
